    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mineral composed of manganese carbonate (MnCO3), appearing transparent to opaque pink to deep red in color; used as an ornamental stone and source for manganese. Found in hydrothermal veins along with other manganese minerals in low temperature ore deposits as in the silver mines of Romania, Germany, and Britain; also found in South and North America.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mineraal dat is samengesteld uit mangaancarbonaat (MnCO3) en voorkomt in de kleuren transparant tot ondoorzichtig roze tot dieprood. Het wordt gebruikt als siersteen en bron van mangaan. Het wordt samen met andere mangaanmineralen aangetroffen in hydrothermale aderen van ertsafzettingen met lage temperaturen, zoals de zilvermijnen in Roemenië, Duitsland en Groot-Brittannië. Het is ook te vinden in Zuid- en Noord-Amerika.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>含碳酸猛(MnCO3)的礦物，礦石成色透明，或為不透明粉紅色或深紅；用途為裝飾用礦石和作為錳礦來源。可見於熱液礦脈中，與其他錳礦物共存於低溫礦床，如羅馬尼亞、德國和英國的銀礦區，同時在南、北美洲都有發現。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
